      "content": "i mean i get that, but just being myself makes everything harder. people react weirdly to me or they just look through me like i'm not even there. it's not just \"pressure,\" it's like the whole world is built for a version of people that i'll never be. it feels like there's no actual place for me to just... exist without it being a constant struggle.",
